==Controversies== Both [[Cycling Canada Cyclisme|Cycling Canada]] and [[USA Cycling]] decided not to attend to the Pan American Championships despite the impact on the [[2016 UCI Road World Championships|2016 World Championships]] and the [[2016 Summer Olympics|Cycling at the 2016 Summer Olympics]] due to the ongoing [[2014–16 Venezuelan protests|Venezuelan unrest]], citing "security concerns".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingcanada.ca/sport/road/news/canada-pulls-out-of-pan-am-road-championships-for-security-reasons/ |title=Canada pulls out of Pan Am Road Championships for security reasons |publisher=Cycling Canada |date=15 May 2016 |accessdate=21 May 2016}}</ref> The location of the championships requires flying to [[Cúcuta]], Colombia then taking ground transportation to Táchira, having the border an ongoing increased violence advice from the Canadian<ref>{{cite news |url=https://travel.gc.ca/destinations/venezuela#security |title=Venezuela |publisher=Government of Canada |date=13 May 2016 |accessdate=21 May 2016}}</ref> and American governments.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://travel.state.gov/content/passports/en/alertswarnings/venezuela-travel-warning.html |title=Venezuela Travel Warning |publisher=U.S. Department of State |date=18 September 2015 |accessdate=21 May 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170616232049/https://travel.state.gov/content/passports/en/alertswarnings/venezuela-travel-warning.html |archive-date=2017-06-16 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> Earlier in the year, during the 2016 [[Vuelta al Táchira]], riders and technical personnel from Italy suffered the robbery from personal belongings<ref>{{cite news |url=http://elperiodicovenezolano.com/robaron-a-italianos-que-participaron-en-la-vuelta-al-tachira/ |title=Robaron a italianos que participaron en la Vuelta al Táchira |newspaper=El Periódico Venezolano |language=Spanish |date=20 January 2016 |accessdate=21 May 2016}}</ref> and Venezuelan rider Carlos Castro had his bike robbed.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.elcorreodelorinoco.com/roban-a-ciclistas-de-la-vuelta-al-tachira/ |title=Roban a ciclistas de la Vuelta al Táchira |last=Ruíz |first=Leonarda |newspaper=El Correo del Orinoco |language=Spanish |date=20 January 2016 |accessdate=21 May 2016}}</ref>
After spending from 13 May to 17 stranded in the Colombian border, cyclists and technical personal from Chile could finally manage to go through and arrived at [[San Cristóbal, Táchira]] on Tuesday 17 May.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cooperativa.cl/noticias/deportes/ciclismo/chilenos/aduana-colombiana-impidio-paso-de-bicicletas-a-seleccion-chilena/2016-05-13/163535.html |title=Aduana colombiana impidió paso de bicicletas a selección chilena |newspaper=Cooperativa.cl |language=Spanish |date=13 May 2016 |accessdate=21 May 2016}}</ref> The Colombian customs authorities denied the passing of goods, but the delegations from Costa Rica, Brazil and Chile were halted in the border and had their practices affected.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cooperativa.cl/noticias/deportes/ciclismo/chilenos/chilenos-lograron-ingresar-con-sus-bicicletas-a-venezuela-tras-varios/2016-05-17/175245.html |title=Chilenos lograron ingresar con sus bicicletas a Venezuela tras varios días de espera |newspaper=Cooperativa.cl |language=Spanish |date=17 May 2016 |accessdate=21 May 2016}}</ref>
During the inaugural session of the championships, protestors demanded in the streets of [[Rubio, Venezuela|Rubio]] were the [[Individual time trial|time trials]] started,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.meridiano.com.ve/otros-deportes/127024/con-la-contrarreloj-inicia-el-panamericano-de-ciclismo.html |title=Con la contrarreloj inicia el Panamericano de Ciclismo |newspaper=Meridiano |language=Spanish |date=16 May 2016 |accessdate=21 May 2016}}</ref> that the [[National Electoral Council (Venezuela)|National Electoral Council]] concede the [[referendum|revocatory referendum]] against Venezuelan President [[Nicolás Maduro]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://elcooperante.com/opositores-aprovechan-inauguracion-de-panamericano-de-ciclismo-para-exigir-revocatorio/ |title=Opositores aprovechan inicio del Panamericano de Ciclismo para exigir revocatorio |newspaper=El Cooperante |language=Spanish |date=19 May 2016 |accessdate=21 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://sumarium.com/piden-el-rr-en-rubio-durante-los-panamericanos-de-ciclismo/ |title=Piden el RR en Rubio durante los Panamericanos de Ciclismo |newspaper=Sumarium |language=Spanish |date=19 May 2016 |accessdate=21 May 2016}}</ref>
