The '''Big Four''' in polo was the American polo team that competed for the [[International Polo Cup]].
==History== The term was first used in 1909 for the team of [[Devereaux Milburn]], [[Harry Payne Whitney]], [[Lawrence Waterbury]], and [[James Montaudevert Waterbury, Jr.]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.westchestercup.org/bio_devereux_milburn.htm |title=Devereaux Milburn |accessdate=2011-03-30 |quote=In 1909 Devereux Milburn played in his first international match with Harry Payne Whitney, Lawrence Waterbury and Monte Waterbury on what would come to be known as the Big Four. |publisher=[[Westchester Cup]] |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120316160852/http://www.westchestercup.org/bio_devereux_milburn.htm |archivedate=2012-03-16 |df= }}</ref> The term was still in use for the 1927 team of [[James Watson Webb, Sr.]], [[Thomas Hitchcock, Jr.]], [[Malcolm Stevenson (polo)]] and [[Devereaux Milburn]].<ref>{{cite news |author= |coauthors= |title='Big Four' Polo Team Will Meet British |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=mxovAAAAIBAJ&sjid=qNkFAAAAIBAJ&pg=3883,3286927&dq=big+four+polo&hl=en |quote=... against the British in defense of the international cup. In the series starting at Meadowbrook September 5. This was announced officially today by the ... |newspaper=[[Ottawa Citizen]] |date=August 23, 1927 |accessdate=2011-03-29 }}</ref>
