A '''ground out''' is a method of putting out a [[Batter (baseball)|batter]] in [[baseball]].
[[File:Ozzie Smith Doubleday.JPG|thumb|right|250px|Ozzie Smith catches a grounder to complete a ground out]]

==Method==
A batter is '''Grounded Out''' when a ball hits the ground immediately after being batted, commonly an [[infielder]] grabs the ball and then throws it to [[First baseman|first base]] to complete the out. It is commonly thrown to first base but exceptions may be when a player is located in first base, [[second base]], or [[third base]] or trying to complete a [[double play]] or [[triple play]].

