{{about|the Bangladeshi organisation|}}
[[File:Bangladesh National Sports Council.jpg|thumb|Bangladesh National Sports Council office at dainik Bangla More]]
The '''National Sports Council (NSC)''' is the national overseer of the control authorities of 41 different sports in [[Bangladesh]]. It is responsible to the Ministry of Sports in [[Government of Bangladesh]] and is based in [[Dhaka]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nsc.gov.bd/|title=National Sports Council-Ministry of Youth and Sports {{!}} জাতীয় ক্রীড়া পরিষদ-যুব ও ক্রীড়া মন্ত্রণালয়|website=www.nsc.gov.bd|access-date=2016-09-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thefinancialexpress-bd.com/2016/09/07/45038/Sportspersons-hold-rally-in-city|title=Sportspersons hold rally in city|website=The Financial Express Online Version|access-date=2016-09-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/frontpage/win-two-countries-1273534|title='A win for two countries'|date=2016-08-21|access-date=2016-09-18}}</ref>

== History ==
After the [[Bangladesh Liberation War]], the Bangladesh Sports Control Board was formed in 1972. This later became the National Sports Council.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Games_and_Sports|title=Games and Sports - Banglapedia|website=en.banglapedia.org|access-date=2016-09-18}}</ref>

