{{infobox country at games | NPC = POR | NPCname = Paralympic Committee of Portugal | games = Summer Paralympics | year = 1992 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.comiteparalimpicoportugal.pt }}&nbsp;{{pt icon}} {{en icon}} | location = [[Barcelona]] | competitors = 30 | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = 29 | gold = 3 | silver = 3 | bronze = 3 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }} '''[[Portugal]]''' competed at the '''[[1992 Summer Paralympics]]''' in [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]]. 30 competitors from Portugal won 9 medals including 3 gold, 3 silver and 3 bronze and finished joint 29th in the [[1992 Summer Paralympics medal table|medal table]] with [[Cuba]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.paralympic.org/portugal|title=Portugal - National Paralympic Committee|website=www.paralympic.org|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref>
